alluxio.underfs.swift

Class SwiftUnderFileSystem

  • java.lang.Object
    • alluxio.underfs.UnderFileSystem
      • alluxio.underfs.swift.SwiftUnderFileSystem

  • @ThreadSafe
public class SwiftUnderFileSystem
extends UnderFileSystem
    OpenStack Swift UnderFileSystem implementation based on the JOSS library. The mkdir operation creates a zero-byte object. A suffix PATH_SEPARATOR in the object name denotes a folder. JOSS directory listing API requires that the suffix be a single character.

      • getBlockSizeByte

        public long getBlockSizeByte(String path)
                      throws IOException
        Gets the block size in bytes. There is no concept of a block in Swift and the maximum size of one file is 4 GB. This method defaults to the default user block size in Alluxio.
        Specified by:
        getBlockSizeByte in class UnderFileSystem
        Parameters:
        path - the path to the object
        Returns:
        the default Alluxio user block size
        Throws:
        IOException - this implementation will not throw this exception, but subclasses may
